This paper deals with graph learning problems, specifically node classification and graph classification, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also proposes a novel semi-supervised solution for these problems, which falls under the category of semi-supervised learning. The use of graph embeddings and self-attention mechanisms also suggests a focus on natural language processing and information retrieval, which are sub-fields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
